ou have discerned, I believe, its permanent value. From this point of view SOLUS REX3 (I shall probably change the title) is a perfectly safe bet. On the other hand, my previous Russian experiences (I am the author of some ten books in Russian) have proved to me that only after one work is published am I freed from its obsession and can attack my next one with real vigor and appetite.

Sincerely yours,





TO: ALLEN TATE1

CC, 1 p.

Cambridge, Mass.





13 October 1946

